It is a chopped up fabricated hot rod with a custom fit engine perfect for a drag car or a builder wanting to do more modifications to a beautiful car with months of work already out of the way. ** THIS IS A PROJECT** And needs a new owner not afraid to tackle all of the small intricate details it needs. It has a set of wide "show" wheels that are wider and taller in the rear, giving it a mean stance; however for clearance issues are only good for rolling off trailer and chugging into a driveway or car show. Rear side window frames have been converted from rolling to fixed during fabrication and the door window tracks are missing/ will require fitting. The gas operated G.43 is chambered for the standard full power 7.92x57mm (8mm Mauser) German service cartridge and features a 10-round detachable box magazine.
